com.github.bwsoft.iris.message

Interface GroupObjectArray


  • public interface GroupObjectArray
    A GroupObjectArray is a section in a message that contains several repeated identical structures. Use getDefinition() to obtain the definition of each identical structure. The GroupObjectArray is the array of this structure, the size of which can be obtained via getNumOfGroups(). GroupObjectArray is also used to add/remove a row to the array.
    Author:
    yzhou

      • getGroupObject

        GroupObject getGroupObject(int n)
        Get nth group object from the array. There is no obligation for the code to verify the existence of the nth object. The behavior is undefined for retrieving a GroupObject out of bound.
        Parameters:
        n - index of a group object
        Returns:
        nth group object

      • addGroupObject

        GroupObject addGroupObject(int n)
        Add a new row to the specific position of the existing group list.
        Parameters:
        n - the nth row to be inserted. It starts with zero and has to be less than the number of rows.
        Returns:

      • deleteGroupObject

        void deleteGroupObject(int n)
        Delete a group object at nth position. It starts from zero and has to be less than getNumOfGroups.
        Parameters:
        n - the row to be deleted
